"a.健壮的，矍铄的 【英】 adj. 健壮的,矍铄的(sound and healthy) 【考】 反义词：infirm(弱的 ); effete(疲惫的); blighted(毁灭的) 【记】 联系词根:hal(呼吸); hale(呼吸得很好的→ 精神矍铄的) adj. (老人)健壮的, 矍铄的 = sound = healthy 【记】hal呼吸e－呼吸得好－精神矍铄的 【反】infirm(adj 不坚固的; 柔弱的); effete(adj 已枯竭的; 衰老的); blighted(adj 毁灭的); anemic(adj 贫血的); wan(adj 苍白的) 【记】源自whole, 近于heal；音：好，好了；问：你(身体)好了吗？答：hale 好了，壮得和牛一样；hale呼吸，象呼吸声，有呼吸就是健康 【相关】另有一个意思，拉，来自于haul；inhale吸气，exhale呼气 hale (adj.)  ""healthy,"" Old English hal ""healthy, entire, uninjured"" (see health). The Scottish and northern English form of whole; it was given a literary sense of ""free from infirmity"" (1734). Related: Haleness. hale (v.)  c.1200, ""drag; summon,"" in Middle English used of arrows, bowstrings, reins, anchors, from Old French haler ""to pull, haul"" (12c.), from a Germanic source, perhaps Frankish *halon or Old Dutch halen; probably also from Old English geholian ""obtain"" (see haul). Figurative sense of ""to draw (someone) from one condition to another"" is late 14c. Related: Haled; haling."
